The paper deals with lower bounds for fundamental problems in computer science, specifically Edit Distance and Longest Common Subsequence, which are typically studied in the context of computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses implications for circuit complexity (cs.CC) and graph algorithms (cs.CG), as well as using techniques from discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and machine learning (cs.LG).
